  "description": "Two side-by-side CTA cards offering the visitor a clear choice — typically self-serve vs. assisted, free vs. enterprise, or audience A vs. audience B. Optional primary-led emphasis tints the first card on bg-primary.",
  "descriptions": {
    "descriptive": "Mirrored card layout with eyebrow, title, description, optional bullet list, CTA, and footnote per side. Two emphasis modes: balanced (both cards on bg-base-100 with a hairline ring) or primary-led (left card on bg-primary, right card neutral). Cards stagger in on view at 80ms intervals.",
    "usage": "Use when the page must offer two genuinely different paths and either is a valid choice — most often self-serve vs. talk-to-sales, but also founder-vs-agency, free-vs-enterprise, or hire-vs-license. Place near the bottom of long marketing pages.",
    "audienceFit": "B2B SaaS routing buyers to the right path, agency sites separating audiences, marketplaces with two-sided users, and any segmented-audience site whose buyers self-identify clearly."
